      "message": "Typo: \"could could\" → \"could\".\n\nMinor logical tightening while you\u0027re here: the section floats \"treat its module as the main module and apply replace directives\" as an option, then concludes that we reject any downloaded module containing local-module.cue. Since such a module can never legitimately carry the file, the floated alternative can never actually arise — so it reads slightly self-cancelling. Consider stating directly that the module is consumed as a (the sole) dependency, so its local-module.cue is ignored like any dependency\u0027s, and separately that the artifact is rejected outright.",
