      "message": "\u003e Typo: \"could could\" → \"could\".\n\ndone\n\n\u003e Consider stating directly that the module is consumed as a (the sole) dependency, so its local-module.cue is ignored like any dependency\u0027s, and separately that the artifact is rejected outright.\n\nI could say that but I\u0027m not sure whether it\u0027s actually true, because internally that\u0027s _not_ actually how it\u0027s consumed, and I\u0027m not totally sure that ignoring local-module.cue does _actually_ amount to exactly the same as that, so I\u0027d prefer to avoid being quite so absolute.",
